Rule Learning, Theory. 

The paper discusses the implementation of a concept learning system that can dynamically modify the set of descriptors used to describe instances in a problem domain. This involves the creation and modification of rules that govern how objects are grouped together based on their attributes, which falls under the category of rule learning. The paper also presents a theoretical framework for understanding the importance of being able to accommodate changing contexts in concept learning, which falls under the category of theory.
